title: Software Engineer Intern
description: An aviation startup in the ground damage prevention space creating digital clones for hangars. I worked on the backend and front-end of their web application for managers to oversee scheduling, template hangars, and account/billing details. I also worked on the iOS application for crew moving planes to be able to see the created templates as well as for near-collision alarms when moving too close to another plane. This application utilized Unity to be able to simulate the hangar in 3D space as well as track collisions.

title: Software Developer
description: Lab at the Georgia Institue of Technology focused on using algorithms and AI to study how social media plays a role in wellbeing and mental health. I worked to create a web application for an opioid use disorder study for participants to be able to view both GPT-4 generated and human written responses related to opioid use. I worked on creating features such as analytics tracking through a custom hook and MongoDB, a quiz system, as well as support for multiple days of responses.
